  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Accounts Assistant (AR / AP)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Responsibilities</strong></p><p><strong>Accounts Receivable (AR)</strong></p><ul><li>Prepare and issue customer invoices accurately and timely</li><li>Perform daily receipts posting and bank reconciliation</li><li>Follow up on outstanding payments and collections</li><li>Prepare AR ageing reports and reconciliation statements</li></ul><p><strong>Accounts Payable (AP)</strong></p><ul><li>Process supplier invoices, payments, and staff claims</li><li>Perform invoice verification, matching, and posting</li><li>Maintain vendor records and payment schedules</li><li>Support month-end closing and audit preparation</li></ul><p><strong>General Accounting Support</strong></p><ul><li>Assist in financial reporting and reconciliation</li><li>Maintain proper accounting documentation and filing</li><li>Support finance projects and ad-hoc duties</li></ul><p><strong>Job Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>Diploma / Degree in Accounting, Finance, or related discipline</li><li>Minimum 1–2 years of AR/AP experience</li><li>Good knowledge of accounting principles and documentation controls</li><li>Strong attention to detail and high accuracy</li><li>Able to work independently and remotely with minimal supervision</li></ul>",
